  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clean Water Needed to Transform Mela Gagula</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The people of Mele Gagula suffer greatly due to a lack of clean water, which presently only 18% of the community have access to. Everyone else travels 3-4 hours to fetch possibly contaminated water from ponds, rivers, and unprotected springs.  Dirty water means sickness, wasted time, missed school and lost hope.  This makes it impossible for the remaining 2,400 people of Mele Gagula to meet their full potential and locks them in a cycle of poverty.  With your help, clean water can end this.</narrative>
  </description>
